input_description:
Input is a sequence of up to $500$ moves, one move per line, until
    end of file. Each move is one of left, right,
    up or down.

The single line of input contains a single string
    $s$ ($1 \le |s| \le 800, s \in \{
    \textbf{a}-\textbf{z}\} ^*$). This is Lulu’s string.

output_description:
Output a single line with the score at the end of the day
    for each of the three contestants, in the order “Odd”, “Even”,
    “Ingmariay”.

Print YES/NO
    if it is possible/impossible to have such a network,
    respectively.
